 served as the 12th <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/United_States_Secretary_of_Energy\" title=\"United States Secretary of Energy\">United States Secretary of Energy<\/a> from 2009 to 2013. Chu is known for his research at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Bell_Labs\" title=\"Bell Labs\">Bell Labs<\/a> in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Laser_cooling\" title=\"Laser cooling\">cooling and trapping of atoms with laser light<\/a>, which won him the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Physics\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Physics\">Nobel Prize in Physics<\/a> in 1997, along with his scientific colleagues <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Claude_Cohen-Tannoudji\" title=\"Claude Cohen-Tannoudji\">Claude Cohen-Tannoudji<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/William_Daniel_Phillips\" title=\"William Daniel Phillips\">William Daniel Phillips<\/a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Nobel_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Steven_Chu#cite_note-Nobel-9\"><span>[<\/span>9<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> making Chu the only <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Missouri\" title=\"Missouri\">Missouri<\/a>-born Nobel laureate. At the time of his appointment as Energy Secretary, he was a professor of physics and molecular and cellular biology at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_California,_Berkeley\" title=\"University of California, Berkeley\">University of California, Berkeley<\/a>, and the director of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Lawrence_Berkeley_National_Laboratory\" title=\"Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory\">Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory<\/a>, where his research<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Steven_Chu#cite_note-10\"><span>[<\/span>10<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Steven_Chu#cite_note-11\"><span>[<\/span>11<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Steven_Chu#cite_note-12\"><span>[<\/span>12<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> was concerned primarily with the study of biological systems at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Single-molecule_experiment\" title=\"Single-molecule experiment\">single molecule level<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-doe_bio_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Steven_Chu#cite_note-doe_bio-13\"><span>[<\/span>13<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Previously, he had been a professor of physics at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Stanford_University\" title=\"Stanford University\">Stanford University<\/a>. He is a vocal advocate for more research into <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Renewable_energy\" title=\"Renewable energy\">renewable energy<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nuclear_power\" title=\"Nuclear power\">nuclear power<\/a>, arguing that a shift away from <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fossil_fuel\" title=\"Fossil fuel\">fossil fuels<\/a> is essential to combating <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Climate_change\" title=\"Climate change\">climate change<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Hebert_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Steven_Chu#cite_note-Hebert-14\"><span>[<\/span>14<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Tribble_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Steven_Chu#cite_note-Tribble-15\"><span>[<\/span>15<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Directors_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Steven_Chu#cite_note-Directors-16\"><span>[<\/span>16<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> For example, he has conceived of a global \"glucose economy\", a form of a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Low-carbon_economy\" title=\"Low-carbon economy\">low-carbon economy<\/a>, in which <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Glucose\" title=\"Glucose\">glucose<\/a> from tropical plants is shipped around like <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Petroleum\" title=\"Petroleum\">oil<\/a> is today.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ontap_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Steven_Chu#cite_note-ontap-17\"><span>[<\/span>17<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> On February 1, 2013, he announced he would not serve for the President's second term and resigned on April 22, 2013.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dixon_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Steven_Chu#cite_note-Dixon-18\"><span>[<\/span>18<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-19\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Steven_Chu#cite_note-19\"><span>[<\/span>19<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-20\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Steven_Chu#cite_note-20\"><span>[<\/span>20<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Steven Chu","place_of_birth":"St. Louis, Missouri","place_of_death":null,"text":"Steven Chu , Physics, 1997","year":1997.0}